TEXT(beginproblem());


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Let the polynomial \(p\) be defined by
\[p(x) = x^3-2x^2+3x+4.\]
Then \(p(x+1)=\) \{ ans_rule(3) \}\(x^3\)
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(1));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
\(+\) \{ ans_rule(3) \} \(x^2\)
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(1));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
\(+\) \{ ans_rule(3) \} \(x\)
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(2));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
\(+\) \{ ans_rule(3) \},
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(6));

TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR Hint: 
The notation \(p(x+1)\) means "replace \(x\) with \(x+1\) in the
definition of \(p\).
EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
We obtain 
\[
\begin{array}{rcl}
p(x+1) &=& (x+1)^3-2(x+1)^2+3(x+1)+4 \\
       &=& (x^3+3x^2+3x+1) -2(x^2+2x+1) +3x+3+4 \\
       &=& x^3+x^2+2x+6.\\
\end{array}
\]


EOT







